    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Gaussian Approximant.}\n\\begin{equation}\nG_{\\sigma}(t)\n=\n\\frac{1}{\\sigma\\sqrt{2\\pi}}\n\\exp\\left(\n-\\frac{t^2}{2\\sigma^2}\n\\right).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Delta Limit.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\delta_{\\mathrm{inj}}\n=\n\\lim_{\\sigma\\to0}G_{\\sigma}(t).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Spectral Law.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\widehat{\\delta}_{\\mathrm{inj}}(\\omega)=1.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nA normalized Gaussian pulse becomes increasingly localized as $\\sigma\\to0$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nG_{\\sigma}(t)\n=\n\\frac{1}{\\sigma\\sqrt{2\\pi}}\n\\exp\\left(\n-\\frac{t^2}{2\\sigma^2}\n\\right).\n\\end{equation}\n\nIn the distributional limit,\n\\begin{equation}\n\\delta_{\\mathrm{inj}}\n=\n\\lim_{\\sigma\\to0}G_{\\sigma}(t).\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe Fourier transform of the delta distribution is constant:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\widehat{\\delta}_{\\mathrm{inj}}(\\omega)=1.\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nA sharply localized injection supplies broad spectral content while preserving local bridge architecture.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
